    {
      "id": "2b18cf01_9960f05c",
      "file_path": "datafile-dmaap-client/src/main/java/org/onap/dcaegen2/collectors/datafile/service/DmaapReactiveWebClient.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 74,
      "message": "The whole idea about ONAP logging specification is to make it machine-readable. It helps to track a request through the whole workflow. The log entries are then indexed by logging framework (Kibana) automatically and thus help to generate different statistics.\nWhenever we have a log entry with RESPONSE_CODE in the MDC, it helps Kibana to automatically understand the status of a request (whereas a request is identified by requestID and invocationID). Of course, we log the status code anyway but that does not make it machine-readable without using MDC.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5051,
        "name": "Muhammad Rehan Raza",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "muhammad.rehan.raza@est.tech",
        "username": "RehanRaza"
      },
      "updated": "2019-03-04 13:15:23.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "7b85ac5a_69a40101",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "08dad26f_2720ba0b",
      "file_path": "datafile-app-server/src/main/java/org/onap/dcaegen2/collectors/datafile/tasks/ScheduledTasks.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 92,
      "message": "Tested with MR/DR simulator scripts to understand the threading behavior and found that the file collection/publishing is done in the same thread. However, when collection/publishing is retried in case of a problem, a new thread handles the retry. Hence, we need to pass the contextMap to file collection and publishing as well, so that the retry can be logged with the same requestID, invocationID (that are passed to DFC when datafile workflow is started)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5051,
        "name": "Muhammad Rehan Raza",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "muhammad.rehan.raza@est.tech",
        "username": "RehanRaza"
      },
      "updated": "2019-03-07 07:42:23.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "f0d2a642_3a4f2177",
      "unresolved": false
    },
